description:
'BACK IN BLUE'

Savage Dragon goes back to his roots! Nearly 12 years after walking off the job as a law enforcement officer Savage Dragon rejoins the Chicago Police Department. It's a great jumping on point for new readers and old, and it helps pave the way for IMAGE UNITED. The Vicious Circle is reborn and Captain Frank Darling turns to the one man he knows can get the job done: The Dragon! It's history in the making, boys and girls! This issue of SAVAGE DRAGON comes with our highest possible recommendation! Featuring an appearance by and an alternate cover featuring President-Elect Barack Obama.

But a daring assault against the Terran Warlord's flagship leaves the rebellion with its most devastating loss yet, while the Klingon warlord Worf himself faces off against his hunted, mortal enemy: Hikaru Sulu.

description: Wiz kid Brigham Fontaine was once Peter Parker's brightest student! Now he's teamed up with Doctor Octopus and is living a life of crime! Will Spider-Man be able to outsmart this brainy duo and get Brigham back on the side of the good guys?

Sam Guthrie (Cannonball) is back home in Cumberland, Kentucky to visit his ailing mother. She reveals that she is suffering from Guillain-Barre Syndrome, a disease affecting the nervous system. She needs to go to Lexington, Kentucky in order to receive treatment. Sam suggests he stay with home to take care of the family.

Cannonball tries to clear his head by flying around his hometown. He sees a glowing girl, Arcadia, running towards the mines where he and his dad used to work. He follows her, only to be ambushed by Ulysses Dragonblood and Arcadia together. Ulysses realizes that Cannonball is not the person that's been tracking. Then the real threat, Argos the Hunter, a member of the Sword, appears and attacks Ulysses. Cannonball knocks Argos out saving Ulysses and Arcadia and asks them who they are. Ulysses reveals that Arcadia possesses a power that Argos' master wants for himself. Cannonball offers his help, but before they continue, the rest of the Sword arrive.

Back in San Francisco, Jesse Aronson (Bedlam) is at a nightclub where he meets a young woman called Kat. However, the introductions are cut short as two special agents arrive to the club to find Jesse. Jesse tries to make his escape by generating his bio-electric fields and shutting down the lights. However, this proves unsuccessful as the agents find him and demand he return with them. X-Force (Siryn, Sunspot, Meltdown, Domino, Monster and James Proudstar) show up to confront the agents. Jesse stops X-Force from fighting the agents saying they aren't the bad guys. The agents state that they are part of M.U.S.E (Mutant Underground Support Engine), an organization dedicated to find mutants in trouble and bringing them to a safe place.

X-Force and the agents go back to their warehouse headquarters where the agents explain their motives. Bedlam was to become an agent of M.U.S.E., but had disappeared, putting them in danger. Bedlam finally reveals why he sought out Domino: he wanted her help to find his brother Chris. The agents insist that Chris actually doesn't exist and that Bedlam made him up.
name: Homefront

description:
At a board meeting of Dacosta International at their San Francisco headquarters, CEO Getulio Villa-Lobos announces he’s contracted professionals to end the threat posed by Reignfire, whom they believe to Roberto ‘Bobby’ DaCosta, aka Sunspot of X-Force.

Outside the burning wreckage of a Las Vegas casino destroyed by Reignfire, the other members of X-Force look on as Bobby hovers above them, fully possessed by Reignfire’s essense. Hoping that the possession has not become permanent, the team attack, but they hold back to avoid injuring Bobby. James Proudstar and Dani Moonstar attempt a ‘fastball special’, with James hurling Dani toward the villain to get a closer shot, but it has little effect. Reignfire then turns his attention to Tabitha Smith (Meltdown), but she defends herself by generating a well-placed time-bomb, forcing him to back off. Meanwhile, Theresa Rourke (Siryn) finds and confronts Dr. Sigismund Joshua, the geneticist who, two years earlier, experimented on Bobby and Reignfire, and who has now come to Vegas to destroy the villain.

Theresa forces him to explain who or what Reignfire is. Joshua descibes his discovery of the the creature, whose body was shapeless ectoplasm, which he dubbed Project Nineteen. While Joshua was experimenting on the captive Bobby, the geneticist had introduced a sample of Sunspot's cell tissue into Nineteen, causing the mass to shape itself into a duplicate of Bobby. Before long, Nineteen had escaped, to resurface months later as Reignfire. Theresa then demands Joshua’s assistance to separate the two mutants. He advises X-Force to simultaneously hit Reignfire with everything they’ve got.

Meanwhile, in the mountains of Latveria, the displaced Locus and Sally Blevins regain consciousness after a backlash of their combined powers transported them there from Vegas. Sally tells Locus they’ll have to cooperate to survive, but Locus lunges at her. Suddenly, both are mystically entranced by an unseen figure.

Back in Vegas, Bobby fights for control of his body, as they crash into an Elvis-themed wedding chapel. The rest of X-Force enter, using their combined powers, which, in concert with the molecular disruptor wielded by James, succeed in exorcising Reignfire from Bobby. Having learned new uses of his power from the villain, Bobby absorbs Reignfire’s heat into himself, restoring his mutant abilities. At this point, a team of S.H.I.E.L.D. agents arrive to take into custody Dr. Joshua and whatever is left of Reignfire.

Some time later, Bobby visits the DaCosta International office of Villa-Lobos. Within minutes, the CEO’s contracted professionals arrive to protect the businessman, but he informs the guardians, who are revealed to be the Heroes for Hire (Luke Cage, Iron Fist, Misty Knight and Colleen Wing), Bobby is not the threat he had believed him to be. After the Heroes leave, Bobby arranges for the release of some of his funds and a lease on an unused company warehouse in the city. Later, the team arrives in San Francisco. Bobby brings them to their new headquarters and surprises them with a planned vacation to Hawaii.
name: The Fire Within

description:
Caliban tracks Risqué to Wacky World, an amusement park where she tries to take refuge.   corners her, but unexpectedly collapses as he did a few days ago.   As she tries to help him, Siryn, Sunspot, Rictor and Meltdown arrive to take her into custody to determine the whereabouts of James Proudstar, last seen with Risqué.  

In a junk-filled warehouse, James wakes to meet his host, the troll-like mutant Sledge, and finds his arm bandaged where blood and tissue samples were taken.   Previously believing himself to be the last survivor of his tribe, Sledge informs him that there is one other, Michael Whitecloud, who may know something of the massacre.   A short time later, X-Force arrives at the junkyard to find James unharmed and ready to go home.   Risque tries to explain to James his abduction was an obligation she owed Sledge, but he turns his back on her.

Meanwhile, at , Domino, returning from South America, is detained by .   He asks for her assistance, and hand her a file revealing Dani Moonstar is a covert agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.

description: There're plenty of gangs in Los Angeles: north of downtown it's the Paid-in-Spades, and down south, past Washington, there's nothing. There's the East-Side Firegirls and Thee Suertes, and past El Pueblo, on the west side, it's the One Tricks. That's what Tubby is, a One Trick, but he's hungry to be someone else, someone out of Los Angeles. He and his girl Vim want to split, but before they can, they need some cash. And that's what the One Tricks got, about a quarter million. If their plan comes off, they're set for life. If it doesn't, their lives don't matter much anyway. After a year-long run in Dark Horse Presents, The One-Trick Rip-Off is collected here in its entirety. It's a tour de force of pure, kinetic storytelling that will keep your eyes peeled until the very last page.

Meanwhile, in the alternate universe of MR. & MRS. SPIDER-MAN, Peter and MJ must stop a desperate criminal - and a future career for Peter Parker is born! The duel universe-spanning epic concludes as the Justice League of America attempts to rally against Tangent Superman. It all comes down to one last-ditch effort as all hope remains with one lone individual. Who's this being, and what's their relationship to the Man of Telekinesis? Follow the ongoing adventures of this modern day 'Flash Gordon' as Amber dreams of leaving her mundane life, but not exactly how she imagined. Dara lost the sword and Victor taste the unstoppable power of it. Now Victor faces his old boss, Knossos, to take control of the organization. While the god and the thug battle to death, Dara realizes that she has only one chance to take back the sword and finish once and for all with Knossos, even if this chance finishes her life.

Before the time of mankind's exodus from the twelve colonies (as told in the current award winning Battlestar Galactica series on SCI FI) and the returned menace of the Cylons, a war was fought between man and machine. A story that has never before been told, until now. Now, Dynamite Entertainment are proud to present the CYLON WAR mini-series event, from writers Joshua (Frank Frazetta's Death Dealer) Ortega and Eric (Halo) Nylund, Galactica veteran artist Nigel Raynor and cover artists Stephen (Wolverine) Segovia (75%) and Nigel Raynor (25%). Fully authorized by Sci Fi and the show producers, the world of Galactica and the first 'apocalypse' with the Cylons is explored here as only Dynamite can!
